    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:1.3",
          "pli": "Atha kho brahmā sahampati abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, the beautiful Brahmā Sahampati, lighting up the entire Vulture’s Peak, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:1.4",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho brahmā sahampati devadattaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:2.1",
          "pli": "“Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti, ",
          "en": "“The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:2.2",
          "pli": "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ; ",
          "en": "as are the bamboo and the reed. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:2.3",
          "pli": "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti, ",
          "en": "Honor destroys a sinner, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn6.12:2.4",
          "pli": "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti. ",
          "en": "as pregnancy destroys a mule.”"
        }
      ],
